ABOUT THE COMPANY AND ROLEThere has never been a more exciting time to join the success of this thriving retailer. Due to its recent steep upward trajectory that is certain to continue, the opportunity has arisen to appoint
        an experienced and highly driven Senior Data Scientist. Reporting to the CEO, this is a truly engaging opportunity in a prominent sector to help drive the business into its next exciting growth phase.As the Senior Data Scientist, you will
        be responsible for conceiving, developing, implementing and providing support and continual updates and enhancements to a range of global leading, proprietary Big Data model systems. Supported by the Data Science team, your primary objective will
        be focused on supporting all areas of the business.DUTIES

Maximise new customer volumes through third party channels and through leads and conversion via sales channels factoring in cancellation and churn rates;
Maximise Life Time Value (LTV) and Revenue Per customer through cross sell and lead targeting;
Optimise the average cost to acquire and LTV per customer through channel analytics, developing a strategy and tactical tool kit and resource allocation;
Continued improvements on existing predictive models currently in production maximising model accuracy and streamlining production code;
Enhancement of existing reporting & analytics for the retention team, providing predictive modelling on customers at risk of churn, to intervene before they do so.
 SKILLS & EXPERTISE

Tertiary qualifications in a quantitative discipline (Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science or Econometrics);
3+ years professional developing, coding, testing and deploying Big Data models;
Strong level of experience using relational databases and SQL querying;
Experience with Python and/or R programming languages;
Demonstrate the ability to handle both structured and non-structured data sources from a variety of sources such as online, XML and through API’s;
Experience with AWS and cloud technologies will be highly regarded;
Strong problem solving and critical thinking skills with exceptional attention to detail;
Exceptional analytical skills to aggregate issues from a wide variety of sources and prioritise and present key messages;
Accomplished finance and management accounting skills; and
Simple and effective communicator to all levels of the organisation, delivering complex ideas and issues simply and powerfully.
 HOW TO APPLYClick the 'APPLY' button and attach a copy of your Curriculum Vitae and covering letter. Please be advised our screening process will take approximately 3 to 5 business days from the date this advert was
        posted, from which time, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.

