FCB Group is a modern group of professional services and technology brands servicing clients in both Australian and New Zealand across all areas of workplace and industrial relations, employment relations, migration, HR compliance and HR technology.
We are looking for a skilled and switched on Data Analyst to join our team at FCB Group. In this role you will be working with both FCB Group’s own internal data, providing insights and metrics to senior leadership as well as working closely with
          members of Professional Services team on auditing processes for our Clients. This position will provide the opportunity for the right candidate to work in a highly skilled team and the opportunity to utilise their knowledge and experiences to
          contribute to the success of the business.
If you pride yourself in the excellent standard of your work but still have fun along the way, then you are the person we want to speak to!
What you’ll be doing:

Analysis of historical and current data presented by Clients, to produce analytical summaries and reports for audit processes conducted by the Professional Services team;
Provide analytics and calculation support to Professional Services team members in wage audit projects, including complex calculations to determine underpayment amounts;
Working closely with senior management to identify key FCB Group data and metrics;
Defining new data collection and analysis processes for client facing and internal stakeholders;
Analysing and reporting results back to the relevant members of the business;
Complete analytics and ad-hoc requests for other parts of the business to provide unique actionable insights on strategic and tactical business initiatives.

Your background will include:

3 years’ experience in a similar role;
Experience working with large scale datasets;
Ability to write comprehensive reports;
Strong verbal and written communication skills;
Attention to detail;
Experience with SQL would also be viewed favourably.

FCB Culture
We offer the right candidate an enviable work environment with a talented, dynamic and outgoing team of professionals to work with and learn from. We value every member of our team and the real contribution they make to our success every day.
          We pride ourselves on operating under 6 core values that include ‘respect for all’ and ‘having fun along the way’, a value which we like to ensure extends to each and every person in the firm.
How to Apply
You can submit your application by clicking on the ‘Apply’ button below and uploading your CV and cover letter. If you would like to contact our team, please do so by emailing Andrew Nguyen at azn@fcbgroup.com.au.
Application from agencies will not be considered. Applicants must be legally permitted to work in Australian on an unrestricted basis.

Australian Rail Track Corporation (ARTC) is a major national organisation with an infrastructure footprint consisting of 8,500 kilometres of track. ARTC is responsible for managing infrastructure maintenance, capital upgrades and the movement
        of trains on interstate railway track across Australia, including the Hunter Valley Coal Rail Network.    The Reporting Data Analyst will provide support to the Long-Term Planning and Reporting team, in monitoring, analysing
        and reporting on the use of the ARTC infrastructure by their customers and respective service providers. This reporting and analysis will provide the business with meaningful operational and commercial insight to compliance and continuous improvement
        opportunities.    Specifically, your skills and experience will include:

Critical thinking and analytical ability to conceptualise, apply, analyse, synthesise and / or evaluate information;
Proficiency using MS Office, particularly MS Excel and other data analysis tools;
Commercial acumen to clearly understand the implications of the data being reported;
Strong attention to detail and communication skills, both written and verbal;
Ability to develop and maintain positive working relationships with a broad range of stakeholders.
 ARTC embraces a diverse workforce to ensure a supportive, flexible and fair workplace in which differences between employees are respected and viewed as organisational assets. They recognise that a talented and diverse workforce is fundamental
        to building a commercially strong and customer-focused organisation that will give rail a competitive advantage. They are committed to hiring the best person for the job, so if this sounds like you we encourage you to apply.           As part of the recruitment process, you will be required to consent to a National Criminal History Check. Appointment is subject to ARTC's medical fitness standards relative to the position. ARTC is a drug and alcohol free working environment.           For a confidential discussion please call Julie Gearie at GWG Partners on 02 4905 0130 or apply with your resume and cover letter before Monday 28th January 2019.

This is a great opportunity for a Contract Analyst who is excited to work in an autonomous role across JANZ within a multi-national consultancy firm.
Client Details
Our client is a multi-national business-to-business consultancy firm who provides services to a diverse portfolio of clients globally. This role being based in Sydney within a small team covering JANZ, our client is looking for a stand out Contract
          Analyst to take charge of the role.

Description
As a key member of the team, key responsibilities will include:

Maintain corporate registers, including business names, trademarks and renewals for all registered companies, assisting with ASIC lodgements;


Monitoring and following up outstanding approvals on a regular basis;


Ensuring that contracts are signed in accordance with internal policies;


Regular liaison with clients, solicitors, court authorities and other stakeholders of varying seniority;


Assisting in contract reviews, updating templates and preparation of documents;


Preparing case briefs and conducting legal research where appropriate;


Maintaining corporate registers, business names and trademarks and assisting with ASIC lodgements, filings and renewals for all registered companies;


Administration duties, organising travel domestic and international, diary management, email management, ad hoc tasks as they arise; and


Preferably not be seeking a career as a practising lawyer.



Profile
The successful candidate will:

Have a minimum of two years’ experience in a Paralegal or Contract Analyst capacity;


Will have exceptional written and verbal communication skills;


Will be confident communicating with stakeholders of varying seniority;


Will be a well presented, organised individual who takes pride in their work and is able to take initiative to prioritise tasks as required;


Will work competently with no supervision; and


Will be career orientated within the administrative space.



Job Offer


Excellent opportunity to oversee legal responsibility for JANZ; and



A great opportunity to work for a globally respected company.



To apply online please click the 'Apply' button below. For a confidential discussion about this role please contact Michael Whitaker on +61 2 8221 8158.

Overview
This Sydney based organisation operates within the dynamic industry of technology manufacturing, import and wholesale distribution. This exciting opportunity will allow Big 4/mid tier first movers and experienced data analysts the opportunity
          to work with an impressive and diverse corporate client base across an array of industries verticals locally and internationally as a Risk & Compliance Analyst

Role overview
Reporting to an experienced GM of Systems and Compliance and a supportive CFO, this newly created role will reward those driven by large data and investigative analytics. The Risk & Compliance Analyst role will largely develop your business
          partnering skills through interaction with the broader organisation and also large Australian and international clients. As you develop. the Risk & Compliance Analysts role will also include:


Managing interactions and project management with large Australian clients;


Negotiating and implementing SLA’s with large clients;


Providing analysis and insights to senior leadership;


Responsibility for product pricing and master data;


Implementing controls to ensuring the accuracy of all product inventory;


Competitor Analysis;


Provide valuable commentary on month to month sales performance;


Heavily partnering with the broader finance team;


Partnering with manufacturing, logistics and operations teams; and,


Assist with ad hoc reporting when required.


The Risk & Compliance Analyst will play an important role maintaining cross-functionality between the finance and operations teams whilst providing key insights into senior stakeholders making this role vitally important to the broader business.


Your background
You will be qualified or undertaking your CA, CFA or CPA with 2-4 years of BIG 4/mid tier chartered accounting experience, OR, you will be an experienced data analyst working with large data sets in an advisory/consulting or risk and compliance
          focused role. Other essential experience and attributes include:


Advanced Excel skills including experience using Power BI tools;


Experience using large ERP systems, experience with Netsuite will be highly regarded;


A history of working with clients in the banking or IT industry will be highly regarded;


An innate desire to challenge and improve processes;


Exceptional written and verbal communication skills; and


An understanding of import and wholesale distribution processes will be highly regarded.



What’s on offer?


An opportunity to work within a well established organisation;


Working within a high energy team under experienced leaders;


Opportunities for career progression; and,


A great location close to a transport hub.



If your background fits the above description and you'd like to discuss the role further, please call Matthew Spence immediately on +61 2 8318 1888

