WorleyParsons is a world-renowned provider of professional services to the resources & energy sectors and complex process industries. Our services cover the full asset spectrum both in size and lifecycle from the creation of new assets to
        services that sustain and enhance operating assets. With approximately 27,000 employees across 42 countries and growing rapidly, we continue to push boundaries and extend our capabilities around the world. We're an ASX-Listed company that prides
        itself on providing safe and high-quality services which exceed our clients' expectations, which is why we manage some of the world’s highest profile projects. At WorleyParsons we are proud of our people and passionate about delivery. WorleyParsons
        is embarking on a significant global project to elevate and enhance the use of data, creating pathways for innovation and linking with our digital strategy. To drive this imperative, we are now seeking to secure an experienced Data Warehouse Architect initially
        on a contract basis to be an integral member of the Data Foundation project. Specific accountabilities include:

 Be the Data Warehouse SME for the Data Foundation project, bringing a strategic focus to how the DW solution will be designed and built;
 Work closely with the wider Enterprise Architecture and Digital groups to define, refine, deliver and manage the Data Management strategy offering specific expertise in the Data Warehouse domain; 
 Ensure the Enterprise Data Warehouse solution meets the current and evolving data ecosystem needs of the global engineering and project delivery groups in addition to the complex and matrixed corporate functions;
 Ensure all data models, and other data ecosystem documentation are maintained to represent the data warehouse and integration workflows accurately;
 Evaluate the ongoing data team resource requirements (internal/external) and delivery schedule to meet business demands within budgetary parameters; 
 Work with the Enterprise Information Architect, the broader Architecture Team and the business to facilitate the development of use cases, user stories, and acceptance criteria.

To be considered for this position you will be Degree qualified in CS/IS with a strong preference for post-graduate qualifications. Some of the skills, experience and attributes we will be looking for include:

Demonstrated understanding of implementation of enterprise architecture frameworks and data governance in a global organization;
 Experience with industry-leading data warehouse and integration platforms, such as Informatica, Boomi, Redshift, Snowflake, Oracle, SQL Server, Teradata, etc. to properly manage teams running the same;
Experience managing a globally distributed outsourced vendor against SLA’s, change control processes, schedules and budgets;
Thorough understanding of enterprise application integration, security, and data platforms, on-premise and cloud-based data warehouses, and data lakes;
 Knowledge of information architectures and structures for Machine Learning applications
Exposure to engineering and design systems such as Hexagon, Bentley, AVEVA, Autodesk would be highly beneficial;
Experience within a large multinational with globally distributed teams;
Sophisticated senior level stakeholder engagement and management skills;
Broad experience with COTS, SDLC, Agile, ADLC, SOA principles and methodologies
When you join WorleyParsons you’ll join an equal opportunity employer that believes in the inherent benefits of a diverse workplace, that promotes inclusion and flexibility. We encourage applications from a diverse population of people that reflects
        the range of countries, cultures and contexts spanned by our operations. We also work flexibly at WorleyParsons and are open to a range of proposals about what arrangements would best suit our people’s needs. To apply for this role
        please complete the online application process through the WorleyParsons website www.worleyparsons.com. You must have current unrestricted working rights for the location you are applying within to be eligible for consideration and only those candidates with appropriate qualifications and experience will be contacted directly.
 
Please note: no agency representation or submissions will be recognized for this vacancy

