Helping to identify analytical opportunities to deliver business objectives;
Developing high value analytical models which deliver insights and enable decision making;
Employing your understanding of statistical and machine learning techniques, such as Time series forecasting, Bayesian, regression and classification, clustering, simulation, and optimisation algorithms;
Leveraging varied data inputs from both internal and external sources.

To be successful you will have:

Tertiary Qualifications in Mathematics, Statistics or Machine Learning; Masters Degree or Ph D preferred.
3+ years of Data Science experience in a technical capacity producing machine learning and other advanced analytics projects in a business context;
Experience in developing models such as ARIMA, Random Forest, Lasso regression, K-mean clustering, linear or non-linear optimisation;
Strong expertise in R and or Python and an ability to write SQL and work with relational databases;
A focus on delivering solutions to problems in a business environment;
A desire to continue to learn and develop your skills as a data scientist.

We’ll take you further by:

Offering competitive salary and bonus structures;
Embracing what makes you unique and leveraging your individual strengths where diverse experience and backgrounds are valued;
Welcoming you to our Actionable Insights Team who by unveiling new ideas, questioning the norm, or solving complex problems are tasked with making an impact on the business that will take us into the future.

